headline: CME Q4 Deep Dive: Retail and Crypto Expansion Fuel Stable Results, New Products Ahead
summary: Financial derivatives exchange CME Group (NASDAQ:CME) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 8.1% year on year to $1.65 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.77 per share was 1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
